    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e5">Figure 145</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f13018e5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13018e5" filename="../figg13/g13018e5.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 145. Main Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft back through the bearing with a soft bar and maul (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e6">Figure 146</hotlnk>). Remove the input shaft from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e6">inset, Figure 146</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018e6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018e6" filename="../figg13/g13018e6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 146. Drive Input Shaft Back Through Bearing and Remove Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the upper countershaft to the right and remove the drive gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e7">Figure 147</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018e7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018e7" filename="../figg13/g13018e7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 147. Remove Drive Gear From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drive the input shaft bearing out the front of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e8">Figure 148</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018e8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018e8" filename="../figg13/g13018e8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 148. Drive Input Shaft Bearing Out Front of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the snap ring from the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018e9">Figure 149</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018e9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018e9" filename="../figg13/g13018e9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 149. Remove Snap Ring From Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft and replace if worn or damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018f0">Figure 150</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018f0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018f0" filename="../figg13/g13018f0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 150. Check Bushing in Pocket of Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front and rear bearings from the left countershaft as described in
                <hotlnk document="s13018_HL1301804.xml" xrefid="hl1301804">REMOVE, COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
